description:
&lt;p&gt;This Primary Care Medical Educator role is responsible for the delivery of quality assured education at Programme and Postgraduate School of General Practice levels across the East Lancashire programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The education will be group based and will be mapped against the curriculum and the needs of the learners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work with the Programme Director and other lead educators to ensure that each learning experience meets the HENW standards for training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will ensure that the organisation of the group learning will be flexible enough to meet the requirements of the learners in their different stages of development and settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder is expected to be on the GMC GP Register with a minimum of one year’s experience in general practice post-CCT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Robert Stokes, GP Head of School&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: Robert.stokes@hee.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GP Team, Email: gptraining.nw@hee.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
